<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN">
<html>
<head>
  <meta content="text/html;charset=ISO-8859-1" http-equiv="Content-Type">
  <title>Gmbal</title>
</head>
<body>
<h2>The GlassFish MBean Annotation Library (GMBAL)</h2>
<br>
Gmbal is a new library for adding GlassFish v3 AMX-compliant MBeans to
GlassFish v3 components. It may be used either as part of GlassFish v3,
or standalone for providing an MBean-based management interface to any
Java application. This is important because a number of modules that
are used in GlassFish v3 are also used independently of GlassFish (e.g.
Metro in OpenSSO).&nbsp; Because of this, Gmbal also runs on Java 5,
while GlassFish v3 requires Java 6.<br>
<br>
The gmbal <a href="http://kenai.com/projects/gmbal">project</a> is
hosted on <a href="http://kenai.com/">Kenai</a>, Sun's new project
hosting site. Available documentation for gmbal includes:<br>
<ul>
  <li>An introductory presentation "<a href="GmbalPresentation.pdf">Gmbal:
Annotations for JMX</a>" which discusses the background and assumptions
of gmbal, and shows screen shots of jconsole accessing MBeans on a
version of the GlassFish ORB</li>
  <li>The functional <a href="FunctionalSpec.html">specification</a>.</li>
  <li><a href="gmbal/javadoc/index.html">JavaDocs</a><br>
  </li>
</ul>
<br>
</body>
</html>

